                            by a buyer to a seller, indicating the type, quantities 
                            and agreed prices for products or services that the 
                            seller will provide to the buyer. Sending a PO to 
                            a supplier constitutes a legal offer to buy products 
                            or services. </p>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr > 
                        <td colspan="2"><a href="Help.asp#f5"> 
                          <P style="MARGIN-left: 650px"><img src="images/Back.gif" width="14" height="14" border="0" alt="Back">Back</p>
                          </a></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="blue"> <a name="four"></a>
                        <td colspan="2"> &nbsp; <b><font color="#FFFFFF">::</font></b> 
                          &nbsp;<a name="PS23"></a><b><font color="#FFFFFF">What 
                          does Purchase order consists of ?</font></b> </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr bgcolor="<%=gsBGColorLight%>"> 
                        <td colspan="2"> 
                          <P style="margin-left:30px" align="justify"> A purchase 
                            order usually contains: PO number, shipping date, 
                            billing address, shipping address, terms of payment, 
                            and a list of services/products with quantities and 
                            prices. It is like an agreement between buyer and 
                            seller. </p>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr > 
                        <td width="92%" align="right"><a href="#four" onClick="window.open('images/Po_3.jpg','GRN','width=620,height=350,left=70,top=50')"><img src="images/snapshot.jpg" width="68" height="16" border="0" alt="Snapshot"></a></td>
                        <td width="8%" align="right"><a href="Help.asp#f5"> <img src="images/Back.gif" width="14" height="14" border="0" alt="Back">Back 
                          </a></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="blue"> 
                        <td colspan="2"> &nbsp; <b><font color="#FFFFFF">::</font></b> 
                          &nbsp;<a name="PS24"></a><b><font color="#FFFFFF">What 
                          is Goods Received Note(GRN) ?</font></b> </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr bgcolor="<%=gsBGColorLight%>"> 
                        <td colspan="2"> 
                          <P style="margin-left:30px" align="justify"> Once a 
                            Purchase Order has been completed the information 
                            sits in the system until the goods / service is received. 
                            Once this has happened and you have an invoice it 
                            is time to complete a GRN. The GRN has information 
                            relating to what has been received, how much and when. 
                            On completion of the GRN a copy is sent to payments, 
                            with the invoice, for payment. </p>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr > 
                        <td colspan="2"><a href="Help.asp#f5"> 
                          <P style="MARGIN-left: 650px"><img src="images/Back.gif" width="14" height="14" border="0" alt="Back">Back</p>
                          </a></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="blue"> <a name="three"></a>
                        <td colspan="2"> &nbsp; <b><font color="#FFFFFF">::</font></b> 
                          &nbsp;<a name="PS25"></a><b><font color="#FFFFFF">What 
                          does GRN consists of ?</font></b> </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr bgcolor="<%=gsBGColorLight%>"> 
                        <td colspan="2"> 
                          <P style="margin-left:30px" align="justify"> GRN Consists 
                            of Items Description, ordered quantity, supplier informaion, 
                            purchase order details, remarks upon GRN Entry. Upon 
                            goods received from supplier / vendor Purchase team 
                            enters the quantity received, quantity accepted , 
                            quantity rejected. </p>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
